killed him a few months ago (when we were just starting HoT) with about 30 people and 3 deaths <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utemraeldarkfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Temrael Darkfury</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/ring20.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/10/02 4:25:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4049.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Lhranc (SK Epic last bad guy)</span><hr size=1> Well we did it.<br>
<br>
We had just over 40 people and he went down like the provebial tanking Ranger. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Our strategy was as I described above, we had about 5 clerics chain casting CH on the MT at 3 second intervals. It was a joy to see the MTs health see-sawing but always returning to full. <br>
<br>
The MT did die in the end, but Lhranc was about 15-20% health and he then turned his attention to others. He turned  to me and before I could even press counterattack I was dead heh.<br>
<br>
But by the time I was back to my bind point the secondary tanks and pets had finished him. There was no Zerg rushing and only a handful of lives were lost.<br>
